Column.name: Note
Column.value:
Definition: A (Debt) Agreement into which is arranged that a party (lender) is giving money or financial instruments to another party (borrower) in exchange for future repayment of the loan value or principal amount, along with interest or finance charges.
Comment: A loan may be for a specific, one-time amount, or it can be available as an open-ended line of credit up to a specified limit, or any other variation. A classification of any agreement that provides funds to an entity in return for a promise from the entity to repay a lender or investor in accordance with terms and conditions of a contract.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party roles involved in the loan agreement like Lender and Borrower.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party roles involved in the underwriting arrangement like Underwriter.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party which provides the collateral. A party can be both a taker and a giver in a collateral relationship. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party roles involved in the collateral arrangement like Giver and Taker.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A Loan Product is a Product offered by a lender (financial institution) to the market, into which money can be borrowed under specific terms and conditions.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
An arrangement within an agreement where an Asset is provided as security for a payment or repayment of an obligation. (BIAN)
Agreement between two trading parties that contains information about their relative duties and rights regarding collateral processes. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
Asset provided by a debtor as security for a payment or repayment of an obligation.
Financial collateral is an asset provided by a borrower to a lender.
The term collateral refers to an asset that a lender accepts as security for a loan. https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/collateral.asp

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A contractual agreement between parties that commits the underwriter to assuming risk.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A specific role of a specific Party in the specific relationship.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party roles involved in the underwriting arrangement like Underwriter.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party roles involved in the collateral arrangement like Giver and Taker.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party which receives the collateral. A party can be both a taker and a giver in a collateral relationship. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Party that is acting on behalf of another party and that offers collateral management services. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: An evaluation by which an individual or an institution undertakes the risk associated with a loan, an insurance, or an investment.

Column.name: Note
Column.value:
Underwriting is the process through which an individual or institution takes on financial risk for a fee. The risk most typically involves loans, insurance, or investments. (Investopedia)
The process during which lenders analyze the risks a particular borrower presents and set appropriate conditions for the loan. (BusinessDictionary)
The process of insuring someone or something. (Investorwords)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: the rating/certification derived as result of an applied test assessment of an entity using specific testing criteria

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A package of services and goods, accompanied by term and condition which is offered as a whole to (internal or external) customers.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A formal or informal common understanding between two or more (legal competent) parties concerning one or more subject matters expressed in a set of arrangements, terms and conditions. (adapted from Legal System and FIBO)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Term and condition to govern the use of loan product and the loan agreement in general.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Amount of money promised to be borrowed.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A desired Amount of loan.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Purpose of loan.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Identifier of loan product.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Date when the asset was provided as collateral

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Classification of the collateral according to a collateral mechanism classification hierarchy. Examples: mortgage, blocked deposit, a blocked securities portfolio, pawn, etc.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A Value amount that is pledged to secure the payments or repayments.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Identifier of the underwriting process.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Result of the underwriting process.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Document that provides background or corroborating information regarding an assessment(s).

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Document that represents the result of an assessment(s).

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Change that the assessment reveals is needed.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Date when the assessment expires. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The identifier of product e.g. ISIN Code.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Specifies the category/type/class of product like financial product. Product can be categorized according to different perspectives.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Refers to the lifecycle of a product (e.g., initiated, announced, active, obsolete, withdrawn).

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A detailed explanation or commentary of product.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Date on which the agreement was signed by all parties. (ISO20022)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Specifies the category of agreement. Agreement type is very often referred to product. But, the term product does not cover all kinds of agreements. An Agreement can be subtyped from the perspective of various aspects of interest. One can classify the agreement from the perspective of format type (e.g., verbal agreement, written agreement). Other one can classify agreement based on duration like short-term agreement or long-term agreement.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: Period during which the agreement is valid

Column.name: Note
Column.value: LifecycleStatus of agreement (e.g., potential, offered, confirmed, completed, signed, terminated)

Column.name: Note
Column.value: The identifier of agreement like Agreement Number, Contract Number, Contract Registration Number, etc.

Column.name: Note
Column.value: A characteristic of agreement which refers to 1) LifecycleDate of agreement (e.g., SignedDate, TerminatedDate, FulfilledDate) OR 2) ArrangedDate of agreement (e.g., StartingDate, EndingDate, ValidityPeriod, EffectiveDate).
